  "text": "A, the pattern of thylakoid membrane proteins before (Ϫ) and after (ϩ) digestion with trypsin as revealed on the silver-stained gel after SDS-PAGE. B, the sequences of the earlier identified phosphorylated peptides [CITATION_1] confirmed in this study and the labeling of these peptides used in the following panels. The lowercase t designates phosphorylated threonine residues, and Ac-designates acetylated N termini. D1 ϩ R designates the N-terminal tryptic peptide from D1 protein with one missing cleavage. C and D, the electrospray ioniza-show that only the first 31 amino acids of the initial translation product of lhcb4.2 are removed during the processing and that the resultant N-terminal arginine of the mature protein is acetylated. We also reveal the in vivo phosphorylation site in the mature CP29 protein from A. thaliana at threonine 6. This is a previously unknown phosphorylation site since the earlier found cold-and high light-induced phosphorylation of CP29 from maize was localized to the threonine 83 [CITATION_2] .",
